import json
async def solve():
    # First, convert characters of "INDIA" to their ASCII values
    input = {"input": {"string": "INDIA"}}
    result = await mcp.call_tool('strings_to_chars_to_int', input)
    ascii_values = json.loads(result.content[0].text)["result"]
    
    # Then, compute the sum of exponentials of the ASCII values
    input = {"input": {"numbers": ascii_values}}
    result = await mcp.call_tool('int_list_to_exponential_sum', input)
    exponential_sum = json.loads(result.content[0].text)["result"]
    
    return "FINAL_ANSWER: The ASCII values of characters in 'INDIA' are " + str(ascii_values) + " and the sum of their exponentials is " + str(exponential_sum) + "."
